<h4>EXAMPLES OF POINTS SYSTEM:</h4>
<p>
Qualification points awarded for 1st, 2nd and 3rd place selection will be Maximum Points less the difference between actual place and selected place
Race points awarded for 1st, 2nd and 3rd place selections will be based on the FIA driver points allocation for each selection.  Where a driver places higher than your selection, you will be awarded the FIA driver points allocation less the number of places the driver placed above your selection.
Race points awarded for a correct 10th place selection will be 15 points.  This is a BONUS points allocation and as such no points will be awarded for incorrect selection.
</p>
<strong>Example 1 - Qualification:</strong>
<p>
If you incorrectly select MAS for Quali 2nd and he comes in 3rd, you will recieve 2 points for that selection (calculation explained below).
Points awarded = 3 (max for Quali 2nd place) less 1 point (since your selection was wrong by one place) = 2 points
</p>
<strong>Example 2 - Race:</strong>
<p>If you correctly select RIC for Race 3rd and he comes in 3rd, you will recieve 15 points for that selection (calculation explained below).
Points awarded = 15 based on FIA driver points allocation for 3rd place
</p>
<strong>Example 3 - Race:</strong>
<p>
If you incorrectly select VET for Race 1st and he comes in 5th Place, you will recieve 10 points (calculation explained below).
Points awarded = 10 based on FIA driver points allocation for 5th place
</p>
<strong>Example 4 - Race:</strong>
<p>
If you incorrectly select ALO for Race 2nd and he comes last, you recieve 0 points for that selection (calculation explained below).
Points awarded = 0 based on FIA driver points allocation for last place
</p>
<strong>Example 5 - Race:</strong>
<p>
If you incorrectly select VET for Race 3rd and he comes in 1st Place, you recieve 13 points (calculation explained below).
Points awarded = 13 based on 15 points max for 3rd place selection less 2 points because he finished two places above your selection.
</p>
